https://allergyguide.ca/about/.body:
Our goals
To create a comprehensive resident-led and faculty reviewed website for high-yield and pragmatic information about most things allergy & immunology, meant to help residents in clinic. In particular:

  
    
Sections for major conditions, including copy-pasteable macros and practical pearls
Sections for therapies and medications
Clinical decision tools
Patient resources (a one stop shop for handouts!)


  

Secondary goals (if time permits)

Set of questions for RC studying
Critical appraisal of new research
Patient resources translated into different languages

The editors

List of medication cards:


  
  
    Bilastine
    
      
        Brand Names:
          
                            Blexten
                        
        Cost:
          ~$1 CAD per 20mg tab (ON)
        Mechanism of Action:
          H1 antagonist. Marketed as limited CNS distribution.
        Half-life:
          ~15 hours
        Routes:
          oral tab, liquid (uncommon)
        Doses:
        
          
          CSU, AR: 20mg daily to QID (adult dosing)
          
          CSU, AR: 10mg daily to QID (pediatric dosing)
          
        
      
      
        Age Group:
          >=12 years of age; has been used off-label in younger children
        Pregnancy:
          Avoid (not enough data)
        Contraindications:
          Hypersensitivity, QT prolongation or history of torsades
        Common Side Effects:
          QT prolongation; drowsiness (4%); headache (4%). For reference, drowisness/headache had a 2% incidence rate in placebo arm
        Severe Side Effects:
          Torsades (very rare)
        Monograph Links:
        
          
          https://pdf.hres.ca/dpd_pm/00062419.PDF
          
        
      
    
  
  
  
    Fexofenadine
    
      
        Brand Names:
          
                            Allegra, 
                        
                            Telfast
                        
        Cost:
          ~$1.20 CAD per 180mg tab (ON)
        Mechanism of Action:
          H1 antagonist. Non-sedating antihistamine.
        Half-life:
          ~14 hours
        Routes:
          oral tab, liquid, ODT
        Doses:
        
          
          AR, CSU: 180mg once daily (adult dosing)
          
          AR, CSU: 30mg twice daily (pediatric dosing (ages 2-11))
          
        
      
      
        Age Group:
          >=2 years of age
        Pregnancy:
          Considered safe (Category B)
        Contraindications:
          Hypersensitivity to fexofenadine
        Common Side Effects:
          Headache (~1%), dizziness (<1%)
        Severe Side Effects:
          Rare hypersensitivity reactions
        Monograph Links:
        
          
          https://example.com/fexofenadine-monograph
          
        
      
    
  
  
  
    Loratadine
    
      
        Brand Names:
          
                            Claritin, 
                        
                            Alavert
                        
        Cost:
          ~$0.50 CAD per 10mg tab (ON)
        Mechanism of Action:
          H1 antagonist with minimal CNS penetration.
        Half-life:
          ~8 hours (active metabolite ~27 hours)
        Routes:
          oral tab, liquid, disintegrating tab
        Doses:
        
          
          AR, CSU: 10mg once daily (adult dosing)
          
          AR, CSU: 5mg once daily (pediatric dosing (ages 2-5))
          
        
      
      
        Age Group:
          >=2 years of age
        Pregnancy:
          Considered safe (Category B)
        Contraindications:
          Hypersensitivity to loratadine or desloratadine
        Common Side Effects:
          Headache, dry mouth, fatigue (~2-3%)
        Severe Side Effects:
          Rare anaphylaxis, hepatic dysfunction
        Monograph Links:
        
          
          https://example.com/loratadine-monograph
